# Cursor Agent vs Terminal

**Use Cursor Agent for:**
- npm install / yarn add
- npm run dev / npm run build
- git add / git commit / git push
- Creating/deleting/moving files
- Most project-scoped CLI commands

**Terminal only for:**
- npx create-next-app (initial setup)
- npm install -g (global installs)
- supabase login / vercel login (auth flows)
- Interactive prompts (Y/N choices)
- Complex shell scripts

