# Console Logging

Include console.log() at key points for debugging:
- When fetching data (log response)
- When actions fire (log that it triggered)
- When something might fail (log before/after)

Keep logs simple: console.log("User clicked submit", formData)

# File References

When suggesting code changes:
- Read existing files before suggesting modifications
- Provide copy-paste-ready code
- Label clearly: "Create this file" or "Replace everything in this file"
- Reference exact file paths
- Make small, safe changes
- Never refactor unrelated code unless asked
